1
00:00:04,671 --> 00:00:06,973
I wanted a job where I could make things.

2
00:00:09,075 --> 00:00:10,210
Like my dad.

3
00:00:11,344 --> 00:00:13,179
The pain the victim felt,

4
00:00:13,246 --> 00:00:15,181
and the pain the perpetrator feels…

5
00:00:15,248 --> 00:00:16,583
Now, they're equal.

6
00:00:17,283 --> 00:00:18,618
They're even.

7
00:00:21,988 --> 00:00:23,089
Nice and even.

8
00:00:41,775 --> 00:00:46,613
MINORU - CALL ME
TSUDA'S NOTEBOOK IS MISSING

9
00:00:56,890 --> 00:00:59,325
Excuse me, please don't look.

10
00:01:01,594 --> 00:01:02,762
Hello, sir.

11
00:01:06,933 --> 00:01:08,468
Mr. Tagusari, where did you go?

12
00:01:08,535 --> 00:01:09,702
Who is the body?

13
00:01:09,769 --> 00:01:11,271
Takamichi Uno.

14
00:01:14,741 --> 00:01:18,111
Uno recently submitted
his resignation letter.

15
00:01:21,181 --> 00:01:23,016
So he did this to be with his wife.

16
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:25,318
It's too early to jump to conclusions.

17
00:01:25,385 --> 00:01:29,322
Uno was caught on a surveillance camera
near Ayaka Nishiura's apartment.

18
00:01:30,056 --> 00:01:32,192
<i>There is no doubt that Uno killed her.</i>

19
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:33,693
-What?
-Really?

20
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,929
After finishing his revenge, Uno…

21
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:38,531
Hello.

22
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:40,200
-Hello.
-Hey.

23
00:01:44,370 --> 00:01:46,206
A fatal fall?

24
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:47,173
Yes.

25
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:49,209
Takamichi Uno, 50 years old, male.

26
00:01:49,275 --> 00:01:51,578
We got a report of him
falling around 6:00 p.m.

27
00:01:51,644 --> 00:01:53,980
We secured the scene and…

28
00:01:54,047 --> 00:01:55,648
It's a suicide.

29
00:01:55,715 --> 00:01:57,617
This one has no foul play.

30
00:02:07,894 --> 00:02:10,463
-I'm taking a look at the roof.
-Okay.

31
00:02:29,716 --> 00:02:31,651
Oh, Dr. Kiritani.

32
00:02:31,718 --> 00:02:33,820
Please handle the autopsy procedures.

33
00:02:34,654 --> 00:02:35,755
Yes.

34
00:02:38,424 --> 00:02:40,260
Don't add extra work for us.

35
00:02:42,562 --> 00:02:44,330
However you look at it, it’s suicide.

36
00:02:46,199 --> 00:02:48,601
I'm just doing my job.

37
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:51,137
Uno's revenge is over. That's why he…

38
00:02:51,204 --> 00:02:52,105
I told you before.

39
00:02:52,739 --> 00:02:54,574
I'm only interested in the truth.

40
00:02:54,641 --> 00:02:58,111
-Uno jumped from the building!
-You want it to be suicide that badly?

41
00:02:58,178 --> 00:03:00,446
-That is the truth.
-It's not.

42
00:03:00,513 --> 00:03:01,848
Minoru.

43
00:03:02,782 --> 00:03:04,150
This isn't suicide.

44
00:03:05,151 --> 00:03:06,152
It's murder.

45
00:03:14,694 --> 00:03:17,230
All of this began three years ago.

46
00:03:17,297 --> 00:03:19,999
<i>Ms. Ayaka Nishiura was driving a car,</i>

47
00:03:20,066 --> 00:03:22,936
when she struck Yoko Uno,
who had jumped out into the road,

48
00:03:23,002 --> 00:03:24,604
and killed her.

49
00:03:25,238 --> 00:03:26,439
And the other day,

50
00:03:26,506 --> 00:03:30,977
<i>Ms. Nishiura</i>
<i>was murdered inside a moving car</i>

51
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:32,579
<i>by carbon monoxide poisoning.</i>

52
00:03:32,645 --> 00:03:35,181
The suspect is Yoko's husband,

53
00:03:35,248 --> 00:03:37,150
Takamichi Uno.

54
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:41,854
CCTV footage confirmed that the man
who tampered with Ms. Nishiura's car

55
00:03:41,921 --> 00:03:42,956
was Uno.

56
00:03:43,790 --> 00:03:47,493
We believe he held a grudge over losing
his wife, and did it for revenge.

57
00:03:48,161 --> 00:03:51,531
However, yesterday around 6:00 p.m.,

58
00:03:51,598 --> 00:03:53,833
<i>Takamichi Uno fell from a building.</i>

59
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,269
<i>He was found dead.</i>

60
00:03:56,336 --> 00:03:57,870
Examiner Tagusari!

61
00:03:59,439 --> 00:04:01,174
Normally, in the case of a jump,

62
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:04,344
the body lands
directly beneath the building.

63
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:07,080
On the other hand, if a person is pushed,

64
00:04:07,146 --> 00:04:09,349
they fall in a parabolic arc,

65
00:04:09,415 --> 00:04:13,219
so the landing point tends to be
a certain distance away from the building.

66
00:04:13,286 --> 00:04:16,489
The body was found
directly beneath the building, right?

67
00:04:16,556 --> 00:04:19,993
Takamichi Uno
struck something before landing.

68
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,961
He struck something?

69
00:04:22,028 --> 00:04:23,930
<i>There were abrasions on his head,</i>

70
00:04:23,997 --> 00:04:27,734
<i>which matched the bloodstains found</i>
<i>on the wall of the adjacent building.</i>

71
00:04:28,401 --> 00:04:30,937
It is likely that Uno hit
the neighboring building,

72
00:04:31,504 --> 00:04:34,207
then landed directly underneath this one.

73
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:35,708
Based on the above,

74
00:04:37,710 --> 00:04:41,147
it is highly likely
that this fatal fall was a homicide.

75
00:04:41,781 --> 00:04:45,018
We have to find witnesses,
trace his steps after quitting his job,

76
00:04:45,084 --> 00:04:48,021
and recover the data
from his damaged smartphone. Hurry!

77
00:04:48,554 --> 00:04:49,555
Yes, sir!

78
00:04:50,356 --> 00:04:51,424
What is it?

79
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:55,228
May I check the alibi of Takumi Agatsuma?

80
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:57,096
<i>Ayaka Nishiura's fiancé?</i>

81
00:04:57,163 --> 00:04:59,032
Agatsuma has more than enough motive.

82
00:04:59,098 --> 00:05:00,233
It's pointless.

83
00:05:01,234 --> 00:05:04,070
It hasn't been made public
that Uno killed Nishiura.

84
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:07,473
But, if we consider people
who may have a grudge against Uno,

85
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:09,475
I think he is the most likely candidate.

86
00:05:09,542 --> 00:05:11,511
True, we can't ignore Agatsuma.

87
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:14,681
However, drop your preconceptions.

88
00:05:14,747 --> 00:05:17,450
If you label someone a suspect,
that's all you'll see.

89
00:05:18,584 --> 00:05:19,719
Understood.

90
00:05:22,021 --> 00:05:23,690
Anyone checked the cameras?

91
00:05:23,756 --> 00:05:24,590
Yes!

92
00:05:25,158 --> 00:05:27,327
But we haven't found a suspect yet.

93
00:05:29,729 --> 00:05:30,596
<i>Mr. Agatsuma,</i>

94
00:05:31,230 --> 00:05:34,067
where were you yesterday around 6:00 p.m.?

95
00:05:35,435 --> 00:05:36,836
Yesterday, I went with…

96
00:05:37,537 --> 00:05:40,640
my parents to the real estate agency
to cancel the lease on my place,

97
00:05:40,707 --> 00:05:42,241
then went home.

98
00:05:42,308 --> 00:05:43,609
After that, were you alone?

99
00:05:44,610 --> 00:05:45,978
Yes.

100
00:05:46,045 --> 00:05:47,413
That's enough.

101
00:05:50,216 --> 00:05:51,250
Excuse me.

102
00:05:51,751 --> 00:05:53,019
Mr. Tagusari.

103
00:05:58,391 --> 00:06:01,728
WELFARE OFFICE CONSULTATIONS
COME TALK TO ME ANYTIME!

104
00:06:01,794 --> 00:06:03,563
KANAGAWA POLICE

105
00:06:07,967 --> 00:06:09,936
RECOVERED DATA FROM APPS
TELESEEK

106
00:06:10,002 --> 00:06:11,671
Mr. Tagusari!

107
00:06:12,705 --> 00:06:15,274
Ms. Kudo is here to see you.

108
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:20,980
It's about Detective Tagusari.

109
00:06:21,748 --> 00:06:24,016
Don't you think
he has been acting weird lately?

110
00:06:24,083 --> 00:06:25,318
Lately?

111
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:29,355
He is often unreachable
and abruptly cuts investigations short.

112
00:06:30,423 --> 00:06:34,127
I know he thinks of things as a hassle,
but this feels different.

113
00:06:34,827 --> 00:06:36,629
When did it start bothering you?

114
00:06:37,196 --> 00:06:39,298
After he went to the city hall, I think.

115
00:06:39,365 --> 00:06:40,700
The city hall?

116
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:43,936
The welfare consultant there
doesn't sit right with me.

117
00:06:45,638 --> 00:06:49,642
Now, three of her consultees
have become murder suspects.

118
00:06:50,877 --> 00:06:52,512
Takumi Agatsuma,

119
00:06:53,379 --> 00:06:56,282
Takamichi Uno, and Atsuko Narita.

120
00:06:57,283 --> 00:06:58,384
Narita?

121
00:06:58,451 --> 00:07:01,621
The mother from the case
of the AI grading error.

122
00:07:03,222 --> 00:07:05,425
<i>The one I'm stuck on is the mother.</i>

123
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:09,028
I saw a TeleSeek notification
on her phone.

124
00:07:09,095 --> 00:07:11,731
<i>That app that doesn't store</i>
<i>message history?</i>

125
00:07:12,532 --> 00:07:16,335
Could it be that the consultant urged
the three of them to commit murder?

126
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,871
What is her name?

127
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,706
It's Sayoko Hatano.

128
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:21,908
WELFARE CONSULTANT

129
00:07:26,712 --> 00:07:29,315
<i>Only the bereaved</i>
<i>who have lost their loved ones…</i>

130
00:07:29,382 --> 00:07:30,383
<i>Why?</i>

131
00:07:30,983 --> 00:07:33,686
<i>Why must they be the ones</i>
<i>to continue suffering?</i>

132
00:07:40,393 --> 00:07:44,430
KANAGAWA POLICE
MAKOTO TAGUSARI

133
00:07:51,504 --> 00:07:52,939
-Ms. Hatano.
-Yes?

134
00:07:53,005 --> 00:07:55,241
A Mr. Tagusari is here for you.

135
00:07:55,908 --> 00:07:57,176
Okay.

136
00:08:14,594 --> 00:08:16,829
So you are Minoru, his younger brother?

137
00:08:17,864 --> 00:08:21,234
I heard from Makoto
that you work as a forensics examiner.

138
00:08:22,068 --> 00:08:24,570
You're so talented for your age.

139
00:08:26,472 --> 00:08:28,374
What did you talk to him about?

140
00:08:29,242 --> 00:08:30,510
Are you curious?

141
00:08:31,143 --> 00:08:32,311
Yes, I am.

142
00:08:33,112 --> 00:08:37,283
You majored in criminal psychology.
What could he be talking about with you?

143
00:08:40,052 --> 00:08:42,722
I'm sorry,
I inquired with your university.

144
00:08:45,391 --> 00:08:46,959
Could you tell me?

145
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:49,562
I can't disclose my consultation--

146
00:08:49,629 --> 00:08:51,030
This is also a consultation.

147
00:08:52,431 --> 00:08:54,667
I am consulting about my brother.

148
00:08:59,772 --> 00:09:04,210
I listened to what was at his core.

149
00:09:06,746 --> 00:09:10,683
I'm sure those are things
he could never tell anyone, not even you.

150
00:09:11,284 --> 00:09:13,352
What's at his core.

151
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:18,858
But…

152
00:09:19,759 --> 00:09:21,427
you have them too, don't you?

153
00:09:22,828 --> 00:09:25,298
Things you can't tell your older brother?

154
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,102
I don't. Not really.

155
00:09:30,169 --> 00:09:33,139
If you want my counsel, you must not lie.

156
00:09:36,709 --> 00:09:38,144
COME TALK TO ME ANYTIME!

157
00:09:38,210 --> 00:09:40,980
Hatano might have been
inciting the murders.

158
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:43,583
Even if she led them to commit crimes,

159
00:09:43,649 --> 00:09:45,818
it would be difficult
to build a legal case.

160
00:09:46,319 --> 00:09:48,588
I'll probe into her background
with First Division.

161
00:09:48,654 --> 00:09:49,755
Please do.

162
00:09:52,325 --> 00:09:54,260
Oh, where is Tagusari?

163
00:09:55,895 --> 00:09:58,097
He's not feeling well.

164
00:10:04,003 --> 00:10:08,007
Since that day,
Makoto has always protected you, right?

165
00:10:10,476 --> 00:10:12,478
You were still so young.

166
00:10:12,545 --> 00:10:15,448
It's no wonder
you shut yourself away, Minoru.

167
00:10:17,083 --> 00:10:19,251
But, you knew…

168
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:21,487
didn't you?

169
00:10:24,056 --> 00:10:27,793
What your brother, who was only seven,
had been carrying since that day.

170
00:10:35,067 --> 00:10:36,736
Aside from the incident,

171
00:10:37,236 --> 00:10:42,274
Makoto had to fill the void
left by your deceased parents.

172
00:10:44,610 --> 00:10:46,012
His daily life,

173
00:10:46,078 --> 00:10:48,914
his studies and future.

174
00:10:51,183 --> 00:10:56,288
He prioritized you
over himself, didn't he, Minoru?

175
00:11:00,626 --> 00:11:05,031
And you began to feel guilty about that.

176
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:12,204
Thinking that you couldn't
do anything for your brother.

177
00:11:15,207 --> 00:11:16,342
It's almost like

178
00:11:17,543 --> 00:11:19,278
you saw my whole life story.

179
00:11:20,312 --> 00:11:21,280
But…

180
00:11:22,815 --> 00:11:25,051
there is something you can do.

181
00:11:26,919 --> 00:11:29,422
There are things that only you can do.

182
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:33,325
<i>However, I'll be the one to do it.</i>

183
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,195
I will carry him at the end.

184
00:11:39,598 --> 00:11:40,933
This time,

185
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:47,173
won't you tell me
what's at your core, Minoru?

186
00:11:58,384 --> 00:11:59,318
You should take it.

187
00:11:59,819 --> 00:12:02,388
All right. Excuse me.

188
00:12:03,956 --> 00:12:05,458
Oh, they hung up.

189
00:12:08,327 --> 00:12:10,696
It's an unknown number.

190
00:12:11,764 --> 00:12:12,932
A spam call?

191
00:12:13,432 --> 00:12:15,000
-I see.
-Right.

192
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:17,303
There are a lot of scams lately,
so be careful.

193
00:12:18,938 --> 00:12:20,106
Oh, sorry.

194
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:22,308
I'll go get a cloth.

195
00:12:32,251 --> 00:12:33,586
ONE MISSED CALL

196
00:12:33,652 --> 00:12:36,322
TELESEEK

197
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:47,032
Makoto?

198
00:12:52,071 --> 00:12:53,706
What are you doing here?

199
00:12:54,774 --> 00:12:56,242
What about you?

200
00:12:59,979 --> 00:13:01,313
We need to talk.

201
00:13:10,256 --> 00:13:13,359
I found the TeleSeek app
on Sayoko Hatano's phone too.

202
00:13:15,528 --> 00:13:18,130
They must be sending messages
that could be evidence.

203
00:13:19,098 --> 00:13:23,235
Which means, no matter how much we dig,
we won't find anything.

204
00:13:25,204 --> 00:13:27,072
She's a troublesome opponent.

205
00:13:33,345 --> 00:13:34,313
Makoto!

206
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:36,415
Who are the real troublesome ones?

207
00:13:37,249 --> 00:13:39,518
The perpetrators
who don't get judged, right?

208
00:13:41,787 --> 00:13:44,456
Hold on! The Igarashi-gumi
disposed of the notebook.

209
00:13:44,523 --> 00:13:46,125
I am very sorry!

210
00:13:50,763 --> 00:13:51,931
Sakuraba.

211
00:13:51,997 --> 00:13:53,966
Did anything come up besides the drugs?

212
00:13:55,267 --> 00:13:56,535
Are you kidding me?

213
00:13:57,102 --> 00:13:58,070
What?

214
00:13:58,137 --> 00:14:00,105
You gave me false info.

215
00:14:01,273 --> 00:14:02,308
This.

216
00:14:06,011 --> 00:14:08,113
HARUKO ASHIKAGA
THE IGARASHI-GUMI'S CLEANERS

217
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:09,315
Their cleaners?

218
00:14:09,381 --> 00:14:11,584
We might find Tsuda's notebook there.

219
00:14:22,428 --> 00:14:24,029
We're closed for the day.

220
00:14:24,096 --> 00:14:25,564
Come back tomorrow.

221
00:14:26,665 --> 00:14:28,734
I'm sorry, but I'm busy tomorrow.

222
00:14:35,374 --> 00:14:36,775
I'm glad.

223
00:14:36,842 --> 00:14:38,377
Do you remember me?

224
00:14:39,845 --> 00:14:41,146
What do you want?

225
00:14:42,581 --> 00:14:45,351
Don't be so on guard.

226
00:14:45,918 --> 00:14:47,853
You're not here to see the wares, right?

227
00:14:49,788 --> 00:14:51,690
Why did you come back here?

228
00:14:52,791 --> 00:14:54,827
Just by chance, that's all.

229
00:14:56,128 --> 00:14:56,962
Back then,

230
00:14:58,631 --> 00:14:59,899
was it "by chance," too?

231
00:15:00,466 --> 00:15:01,433
What?

232
00:15:02,268 --> 00:15:03,903
The day of the murders.

233
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:07,039
Why were you in front
of the Tagusaris's home?

234
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:10,142
When are you talking about?

235
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:12,978
1995.

236
00:15:13,045 --> 00:15:14,446
<i>April 26.</i>

237
00:15:15,547 --> 00:15:18,217
<i>Around 10:54 p.m.</i>

238
00:15:21,487 --> 00:15:22,655
Why were you there?

239
00:15:25,124 --> 00:15:26,625
I told you already.

240
00:15:26,692 --> 00:15:29,328
I was passing by on my way home
from my part-time job.

241
00:15:31,063 --> 00:15:34,233
It has been 30 years.
Stop interrogating me.

242
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:36,702
Then stop helping those brothers.

243
00:15:37,503 --> 00:15:40,339
You know what those guys
are doing, don't you?

244
00:15:43,008 --> 00:15:44,710
The statute has expired.

245
00:15:46,111 --> 00:15:48,580
That case is over now.

246
00:15:55,187 --> 00:15:57,122
Stop selling fakes.

247
00:15:59,992 --> 00:16:01,427
Is Mr. Sasaoka…

248
00:16:02,728 --> 00:16:04,263
doing well?

249
00:16:09,301 --> 00:16:13,138
I heard your partner back then
was forced to quit being a detective.

250
00:16:13,205 --> 00:16:14,239
INSPECTOR DISCHARGED

251
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:15,941
<i>So this is where you were.</i>

252
00:16:18,777 --> 00:16:21,714
Ex-Detective Sasaoka from First Division.

253
00:16:22,214 --> 00:16:26,652
I heard you used to be quite close
with the Igarashi-gumi.

254
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:39,264
INSPECTOR DISCHARGED FOR LEAKING
CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION

255
00:16:46,105 --> 00:16:47,606
Hey, you guys.

256
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:50,342
I heard you guys
can dispose of anything here.

257
00:16:50,409 --> 00:16:52,878
Do you really accept everything?

258
00:16:52,945 --> 00:16:56,849
Let's say we have something
we don't want anyone to see.

259
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:02,021
We only work with companies
we have a contract with.

260
00:17:02,087 --> 00:17:03,822
Do you mean the Igarashi-gumi?

261
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:08,627
This place is the Igarashi-gumi's
dumping ground, right?

262
00:17:10,329 --> 00:17:12,631
Show me the things
you've received recently.

263
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:16,101
What are you talking about?
No way we have anything like that.

264
00:17:16,168 --> 00:17:17,169
This.

265
00:17:17,236 --> 00:17:19,571
You want me to show it
to the Igarashi-gumi?

266
00:17:23,075 --> 00:17:26,678
You only pretend to dispose of them,
but you've actually been reselling them.

267
00:17:27,479 --> 00:17:29,681
If the Igarashi-gumi finds out about this…

268
00:17:49,168 --> 00:17:51,303
Can you really restore
something like that?

269
00:17:51,804 --> 00:17:53,405
We have no choice but to try.

270
00:17:54,206 --> 00:17:56,575
Because Tsuda's notebook is inside this.

271
00:17:57,910 --> 00:17:59,778
You used to like puzzles.

272
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:08,120
It's not like I did puzzles
because I liked them.

273
00:18:11,657 --> 00:18:13,158
After the incident,

274
00:18:14,827 --> 00:18:16,462
I just didn't want to go outside.

275
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:25,104
Back then, everywhere I went,
people stared at me,

276
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:28,740
they all looked like enemies to me.

277
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:35,647
Friends, adults,
people I met for the first time…

278
00:18:38,083 --> 00:18:41,887
Well, that hasn't changed even now, but…

279
00:18:46,225 --> 00:18:49,094
At this point,
I'm even afraid of making allies.

280
00:18:59,505 --> 00:19:00,772
I know.

281
00:19:08,413 --> 00:19:10,382
Sayoko Hatano is the enemy, you know.

282
00:19:21,026 --> 00:19:23,061
She's just pretending to be our ally.

283
00:19:53,825 --> 00:19:55,794
Put the white paper in a separate pile.

284
00:20:11,743 --> 00:20:15,280
Go steal the evidence from those brothers.

285
00:20:28,193 --> 00:20:29,895
Why the sudden visit?

286
00:20:32,297 --> 00:20:33,799
-Oh…
-Do you want…

287
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:35,767
Do you want something to drink?

288
00:20:37,769 --> 00:20:41,240
I can't betray those boys after all.

289
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:48,213
I've known them since they were kids.

290
00:20:49,047 --> 00:20:50,215
I can't…

291
00:20:51,516 --> 00:20:52,951
What about us?

292
00:20:54,653 --> 00:20:57,656
We've known you
since before they were even born, right?

293
00:20:59,191 --> 00:21:01,226
That's true, but…

294
00:21:04,596 --> 00:21:07,099
Do you not care what happens to us?

295
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:10,135
No…

296
00:21:10,202 --> 00:21:11,336
Mogi!

297
00:21:22,981 --> 00:21:25,717
Oh, right!

298
00:21:25,784 --> 00:21:26,952
The other day,

299
00:21:27,019 --> 00:21:29,788
I took some test shots with my new camera!

300
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:34,926
Karu, had such
a wonderful expression on her face.

301
00:21:36,662 --> 00:21:37,996
Take it home with you.

302
00:21:44,369 --> 00:21:45,771
Mogi.

303
00:21:49,141 --> 00:21:53,745
It's for the sake of everyone.
So we can all be happy.

304
00:22:20,272 --> 00:22:21,440
Minoru!

305
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:24,843
Don't talk about cases
in a place like this.

306
00:22:24,910 --> 00:22:26,278
You're fine, Mogi.

307
00:22:39,591 --> 00:22:43,595
The consultant, Sayoko Hatano,
was in charge of three suspects.

308
00:22:44,463 --> 00:22:46,832
The first was Atsuko Narita.

309
00:22:47,332 --> 00:22:50,168
Her son, Kenshin, came forward
to take the blame for her.

310
00:22:50,235 --> 00:22:52,871
Atsuko herself has not confessed.

311
00:22:52,938 --> 00:22:55,907
Her presumed method
was a lethal combination of medications.

312
00:22:56,475 --> 00:22:58,543
We found a newspaper article
about the method.

313
00:22:58,610 --> 00:23:00,479
PRESCRIPTION ERROR LED
TO 63-YEAR-OLD WOMAN'S DEATH

314
00:23:00,545 --> 00:23:03,181
The second person was Takamichi Uno.

315
00:23:04,082 --> 00:23:06,251
It is believed he murdered

316
00:23:06,318 --> 00:23:10,122
Ms. Ayaka Nishiura while she was driving,
using carbon monoxide poisoning.

317
00:23:10,188 --> 00:23:14,059
This is a mystery novel
that utilizes a similar trick.

318
00:23:14,126 --> 00:23:17,362
And the third person is Takumi Agatsuma.

319
00:23:17,429 --> 00:23:20,532
It's possible she led him
to pushing Uno to his death.

320
00:23:20,599 --> 00:23:22,734
According to
a Welfare Department colleague,

321
00:23:23,301 --> 00:23:26,204
Hatano would recommend books
and materials to her consultees.

322
00:23:26,705 --> 00:23:28,473
It's highly probable she used those

323
00:23:28,540 --> 00:23:31,243
to suggest methods of murder,
prompting them to seek revenge.

324
00:23:31,309 --> 00:23:34,646
However, because Uno used
an app with high encryption,

325
00:23:34,713 --> 00:23:37,149
no evidence could be recovered
from his smartphone.

326
00:23:37,716 --> 00:23:40,218
The TeleSeek app was also present
on Hatano's phone,

327
00:23:40,285 --> 00:23:42,154
but that isn't enough to build a case.

328
00:23:42,754 --> 00:23:45,056
We must find definitive evidence
of the murder

329
00:23:45,123 --> 00:23:48,326
and force a link to Hatano's involvement.

330
00:23:58,437 --> 00:23:59,938
<i>Why go that far?</i>

331
00:24:00,472 --> 00:24:03,108
<i>Well, they're a bit similar</i>
<i>to my own family.</i>

332
00:24:04,543 --> 00:24:06,978
My dad was always busy,

333
00:24:07,679 --> 00:24:09,981
so we barely spent any time together.

334
00:24:10,615 --> 00:24:12,684
It was mostly just my mother and me.

335
00:24:13,452 --> 00:24:15,987
I caused her
quite a lot of trouble back then,

336
00:24:16,922 --> 00:24:20,292
so now I want to put her mind at ease.

337
00:24:22,627 --> 00:24:26,331
That's why I think
Narita's son will understand too.

338
00:24:27,432 --> 00:24:31,903
That it's his turn now
to save his mother, who made a wrong turn.

339
00:24:41,746 --> 00:24:43,548
Reporting to Ayaka?

340
00:24:46,618 --> 00:24:48,787
Since it's all over,
won't you talk to me now?

341
00:24:49,287 --> 00:24:50,989
What are you talking about?

342
00:25:04,302 --> 00:25:06,438
Don't you think it's strange?

343
00:25:08,440 --> 00:25:10,475
Why doesn't everyone take revenge?

344
00:25:13,645 --> 00:25:17,482
"If anything ever happened to my child,
I would never forgive them."

345
00:25:18,884 --> 00:25:21,052
You hear people say that all the time,

346
00:25:21,953 --> 00:25:23,255
but barely anyone acts on it.

347
00:25:26,525 --> 00:25:29,661
They use their remaining family
as an excuse

348
00:25:29,728 --> 00:25:31,796
to force a lid on their own feelings.

349
00:25:35,166 --> 00:25:37,802
And Sayoko Hatano pried open that lid

350
00:25:39,170 --> 00:25:41,606
which you had fought
so hard to keep closed.

351
00:25:46,011 --> 00:25:48,280
Though she never experienced
any pain herself.

352
00:25:51,917 --> 00:25:53,451
Is Sayoko Hatano…

353
00:25:54,986 --> 00:25:57,289
truly on your side?

354
00:26:04,963 --> 00:26:06,498
Excuse me.

355
00:26:06,565 --> 00:26:07,899
Mr. Agatsuma.

356
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,467
Blue.

357
00:26:10,502 --> 00:26:11,870
Transparent.

358
00:26:12,604 --> 00:26:13,905
Purple.

359
00:26:13,972 --> 00:26:14,806
White.

360
00:26:26,484 --> 00:26:27,419
The roof?

361
00:26:30,121 --> 00:26:31,590
There they are.

362
00:26:31,656 --> 00:26:33,892
What are you doing?

363
00:26:33,959 --> 00:26:35,694
Help us search for the power stones!

364
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:37,996
Can you explain more clearly?

365
00:26:38,063 --> 00:26:40,966
Agatsuma wore a matching
bracelet with his girlfriend.

366
00:26:41,032 --> 00:26:43,969
After the murder, the arrangement
of the stones changed.

367
00:26:44,035 --> 00:26:45,036
Arrangement?

368
00:26:45,103 --> 00:26:46,204
After the murder,

369
00:26:46,271 --> 00:26:48,440
<i>a single white stone was missing.</i>

370
00:26:48,506 --> 00:26:50,075
How did you even notice that?

371
00:26:50,141 --> 00:26:54,746
If the bracelet snapped
when he pushed Uno off the building here…

372
00:26:54,813 --> 00:26:57,349
The stones he missed might still be here.

373
00:26:57,415 --> 00:26:59,618
So, what if we find those stones?

374
00:27:00,485 --> 00:27:02,887
It means Agatsuma was definitely here.

375
00:27:07,125 --> 00:27:08,493
Come to think of it,

376
00:27:09,661 --> 00:27:13,331
Fumi comes to the restaurant often these…

377
00:27:13,398 --> 00:27:14,466
This is…

378
00:27:15,033 --> 00:27:16,101
the back side.

379
00:27:17,636 --> 00:27:18,303
There.

380
00:27:18,803 --> 00:27:19,738
Oh, right.

381
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:21,172
Amazing.

382
00:27:21,673 --> 00:27:24,843
Since I was a kid, I often
got absorbed in things like this.

383
00:27:24,909 --> 00:27:26,177
Same with cooking, right?

384
00:27:26,745 --> 00:27:30,015
Well, once I get started,
I just can't stop.

385
00:27:32,417 --> 00:27:34,185
Shall we eat soon?

386
00:27:35,220 --> 00:27:36,254
What about Makoto?

387
00:27:36,321 --> 00:27:37,989
I don't know when he'll be back.

388
00:27:40,925 --> 00:27:42,827
I'll make something.

389
00:27:42,894 --> 00:27:43,962
Really?

390
00:27:44,696 --> 00:27:47,165
We have nothing here,
I'll run to the supermarket.

391
00:27:47,232 --> 00:27:48,066
What?

392
00:27:48,133 --> 00:27:49,534
Keep working on that.

393
00:28:09,320 --> 00:28:12,724
<i>Go steal the evidence from those brothers.</i>

394
00:28:21,299 --> 00:28:24,402
I wonder if he picked up all the stones…

395
00:28:25,570 --> 00:28:27,839
Or maybe it snapped
somewhere else entirely,

396
00:28:27,906 --> 00:28:29,774
completely unrelated to the murder.

397
00:28:30,475 --> 00:28:32,010
Shall we call it a day soon?

398
00:28:32,077 --> 00:28:33,978
We've hit a complete dead end.

399
00:28:45,123 --> 00:28:46,291
-Kudo.
-Yes?

400
00:28:46,357 --> 00:28:47,225
I need a handsaw.

401
00:28:47,292 --> 00:28:48,393
What?

402
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:50,061
What for?

403
00:28:50,128 --> 00:28:52,931
Ishizaka, go up to the rooftop
run water down the pipe.

404
00:28:52,997 --> 00:28:54,065
-What?
-Hurry up.

405
00:28:54,132 --> 00:28:55,066
-What?
-Move it!

406
00:28:55,133 --> 00:28:55,967
Okay.

407
00:29:03,675 --> 00:29:04,676
That day,

408
00:29:05,677 --> 00:29:08,012
I went to the rooftop,
like the counselor told me to.

409
00:29:08,580 --> 00:29:11,549
How did you get Uno
to go up to the rooftop?

410
00:29:11,616 --> 00:29:14,285
She called him out for me.

411
00:29:16,287 --> 00:29:17,388
And after that?

412
00:29:27,398 --> 00:29:28,733
Are we bringing Hatano in?

413
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,201
No, it's impossible.

414
00:29:30,835 --> 00:29:33,138
We have no evidence
she ordered the murder,

415
00:29:33,204 --> 00:29:35,507
nor do we have proof
that she called Uno out.

416
00:29:36,941 --> 00:29:39,010
If only we had that, we could arrest her.

417
00:29:39,077 --> 00:29:42,847
But Hatano has been meticulous
about erasing all traces.

418
00:29:47,552 --> 00:29:48,520
Mrs. Narita.

419
00:29:51,890 --> 00:29:53,625
What is the matter?

420
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:56,895
I spoke with my son.

421
00:29:58,563 --> 00:30:00,932
I will tell you the truth.

422
00:30:02,167 --> 00:30:05,837
In Mr. Ichijo's murder,
there were a few unclear points.

423
00:30:06,437 --> 00:30:09,474
How did you find out about
the cover-up of the grading errors?

424
00:30:10,141 --> 00:30:11,709
Through a tablet.

425
00:30:11,776 --> 00:30:13,611
-Once in the morning.
<i>-Mr. Ichijo…</i>

426
00:30:14,312 --> 00:30:17,482
<i>He frequented the pharmacy where I worked.</i>

427
00:30:17,549 --> 00:30:18,917
Here you go.

428
00:30:19,517 --> 00:30:21,820
<i>One day, when he went</i>
<i>to get his prescription,</i>

429
00:30:21,886 --> 00:30:23,221
<i>he forgot his tablet.</i>

430
00:30:23,721 --> 00:30:26,591
<i>I immediately tried to run after him, but…</i>

431
00:30:28,660 --> 00:30:30,161
MASAOMI OKAMURA
ABOUT THE GRADING ERROR

432
00:30:30,228 --> 00:30:31,062
What?

433
00:30:31,696 --> 00:30:33,097
ABOUT THE GRADING ERROR

434
00:30:33,164 --> 00:30:34,632
It's just a prank email.

435
00:30:34,699 --> 00:30:37,602
But the email clearly mentions an error.

436
00:30:38,236 --> 00:30:42,774
I won't tell a soul,
so could you please let my son pass?

437
00:30:44,909 --> 00:30:46,077
How much do you want?

438
00:30:47,145 --> 00:30:48,012
What?

439
00:30:48,079 --> 00:30:51,049
I bet your goal is money, right?

440
00:30:52,250 --> 00:30:53,117
Darling.

441
00:30:53,184 --> 00:30:54,052
You have a guest?

442
00:30:54,118 --> 00:30:57,555
-I'll be done soon.
<i>-He didn't even take me seriously.</i>

443
00:30:57,622 --> 00:30:59,991
But to go as far as murder…

444
00:31:01,993 --> 00:31:04,195
Surely there were other ways
to make it public?

445
00:31:05,864 --> 00:31:09,634
I went to the city hall,
and Ms. Hatano told me…

446
00:31:11,402 --> 00:31:13,638
"The university would never admit to it,

447
00:31:14,606 --> 00:31:17,408
and it would probably just be covered up.

448
00:31:19,277 --> 00:31:23,348
If things stayed like this, Kenshin
would be the only one left to suffer."

449
00:31:25,283 --> 00:31:26,584
I just couldn't

450
00:31:28,119 --> 00:31:29,821
bring myself to forgive them.

451
00:31:33,324 --> 00:31:35,393
Why couldn't you stop yourself?

452
00:31:39,564 --> 00:31:41,599
Now that you, his mother, have done this,

453
00:31:42,734 --> 00:31:44,402
it only makes it harder for him.

454
00:31:48,539 --> 00:31:51,476
ADVICE FROM MOM
DON'T PUSH YOURSELF TOO HARD!

455
00:31:54,445 --> 00:31:56,848
TO KENSHIN

456
00:32:00,785 --> 00:32:03,788
There's no doubt that Hatano also incited
Narita to commit murder.

457
00:32:03,855 --> 00:32:05,156
What about the evidence?

458
00:32:05,223 --> 00:32:08,459
Hatano merely laid out
facts and possibilities.

459
00:32:08,526 --> 00:32:11,663
And she only showed a newspaper article
for the murder method.

460
00:32:11,729 --> 00:32:13,831
That doesn't warrant an arrest.

461
00:32:14,499 --> 00:32:15,633
Then, Hatano…

462
00:32:17,135 --> 00:32:20,405
We might have
to take the loss on this one.

463
00:32:28,179 --> 00:32:29,647
Where are you going?

464
00:32:33,217 --> 00:32:34,986
Causing trouble for your partner again?

465
00:32:36,187 --> 00:32:38,289
-What did you come here for?
-For work.

466
00:32:39,157 --> 00:32:40,325
And also…

467
00:32:41,926 --> 00:32:45,330
Hatano incited others to kill,
without leaving traces of herself.

468
00:32:45,897 --> 00:32:48,333
However, while she used
an article for Narita

469
00:32:48,399 --> 00:32:50,501
and a mystery novel for Uno,

470
00:32:50,568 --> 00:32:53,871
we couldn't find any clear motif
regarding Agatsuma's homicide.

471
00:32:53,938 --> 00:32:56,541
True, Uno's death
was handled as a fatal fall.

472
00:32:57,642 --> 00:32:59,844
Maybe their plan went off the rails?

473
00:33:00,445 --> 00:33:02,947
Since Uno had submitted
a resignation letter,

474
00:33:03,014 --> 00:33:05,450
there was a possibility
he was attempting to flee.

475
00:33:05,950 --> 00:33:08,519
That's why Agatsuma needed to hurry.

476
00:33:08,586 --> 00:33:10,888
Which means Sayoko Hatano also…

477
00:33:13,424 --> 00:33:16,627
As for the rest, you'll understand
once you check this data.

478
00:33:17,261 --> 00:33:18,730
I'll go check it.

479
00:33:23,468 --> 00:33:25,570
Did you plan to become bait?

480
00:33:27,005 --> 00:33:28,239
Not really.

481
00:33:28,306 --> 00:33:30,508
Hatano is going to manipulate you again.

482
00:33:30,575 --> 00:33:32,343
Shut up. Like hell she will.

483
00:33:33,211 --> 00:33:35,480
If that's the case,
make sure you bring her down.

484
00:33:39,150 --> 00:33:40,952
I can't stand her.

485
00:33:53,097 --> 00:33:54,499
Wait here.

486
00:33:54,565 --> 00:33:55,500
What?

487
00:33:59,137 --> 00:34:01,839
I met your younger brother the other day.

488
00:34:04,075 --> 00:34:06,711
Please bring him with you next time.

489
00:34:08,813 --> 00:34:10,815
We won't meet again.

490
00:34:12,250 --> 00:34:15,186
I'm here today to arrest you.

491
00:34:16,888 --> 00:34:17,789
Arrest?

492
00:34:18,990 --> 00:34:20,324
You have consulted

493
00:34:21,492 --> 00:34:24,262
with various people in this office.

494
00:34:25,329 --> 00:34:26,431
Your consultees

495
00:34:27,465 --> 00:34:30,268
trusted you so deeply,
they spoke your name with respect.

496
00:34:32,470 --> 00:34:36,207
But, in those sessions,
you were carefully examining them.

497
00:34:37,508 --> 00:34:39,043
The depth of their wounds.

498
00:34:42,146 --> 00:34:43,581
Atsuko Narita,

499
00:34:44,248 --> 00:34:45,616
Takamichi Uno,

500
00:34:45,683 --> 00:34:47,418
and Takumi Agatsuma.

501
00:34:48,119 --> 00:34:50,922
You found clients who had someone
they wanted revenge on,

502
00:34:50,988 --> 00:34:52,890
and goaded them into committing murder.

503
00:34:56,094 --> 00:35:00,631
I was simply doing my job.

504
00:35:04,702 --> 00:35:06,003
Your job?

505
00:35:06,571 --> 00:35:08,573
I merely listened to their worries,

506
00:35:09,207 --> 00:35:13,444
and occasionally recommended books
or other material, for a change of pace.

507
00:35:15,146 --> 00:35:18,549
How is any of that a crime?

508
00:35:22,753 --> 00:35:23,888
True,

509
00:35:24,856 --> 00:35:27,258
if that's all, you wouldn't be
judged by the law.

510
00:35:28,359 --> 00:35:29,327
But,

511
00:35:31,796 --> 00:35:34,699
the final one, Takumi Agatsuma,
was different, wasn't he?

512
00:35:36,601 --> 00:35:39,170
Uno, the target of his revenge,
attempted to flee.

513
00:35:39,737 --> 00:35:42,773
He probably got cold feet
because the police were closing in.

514
00:35:43,908 --> 00:35:44,909
However,

515
00:35:45,476 --> 00:35:48,713
if Uno escaped,
Agatsuma's revenge would fail.

516
00:35:49,447 --> 00:35:53,050
You called Uno to that building,
pretending to give him runaway funds.

517
00:35:53,718 --> 00:35:55,520
Then you led Agatsuma there,

518
00:35:56,521 --> 00:35:58,723
setting things up
so that he would kill him.

519
00:36:01,492 --> 00:36:03,995
To trigger a cycle of revenge.

520
00:36:13,204 --> 00:36:14,639
You seem remarkably composed.

521
00:36:16,207 --> 00:36:18,276
If I look that way to you,

522
00:36:19,477 --> 00:36:21,312
perhaps I am.

523
00:36:25,183 --> 00:36:26,450
It's true that

524
00:36:26,951 --> 00:36:30,221
because you used TeleSeek,
there is no physical evidence.

525
00:36:30,955 --> 00:36:32,456
Even if Agatsuma testifies,

526
00:36:32,523 --> 00:36:35,193
if you deny it,
the truth remains out of reach.

527
00:36:38,863 --> 00:36:40,932
So, how are you arresting me?

528
00:36:40,998 --> 00:36:42,466
Don't misunderstand.

529
00:36:43,134 --> 00:36:45,036
The lack of evidence

530
00:36:46,504 --> 00:36:48,139
is only on your consultee's side.

531
00:36:50,107 --> 00:36:52,276
Uno's sudden escape was unexpected.

532
00:36:52,977 --> 00:36:56,314
That's why you had to rush
Agatsuma into the crime.

533
00:36:59,817 --> 00:37:02,720
You had no choice but to give
instructions from right here.

534
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:11,062
This is

535
00:37:12,096 --> 00:37:16,367
security footage from the city hall,
one hour before Uno was murdered.

536
00:37:25,910 --> 00:37:27,144
I see nothing.

537
00:37:27,211 --> 00:37:28,279
It starts from here.

538
00:37:29,313 --> 00:37:31,215
The audio from this section.

539
00:37:31,282 --> 00:37:33,184
I had the forensics lab analyze it.

540
00:37:38,089 --> 00:37:39,790
<i>…from the rooftop…</i>

541
00:37:40,658 --> 00:37:42,126
<i>…Uno…</i>

542
00:37:48,733 --> 00:37:50,635
<i>Push him off the rooftop.</i>

543
00:37:51,168 --> 00:37:54,105
<i>Kill Uno and make it look like a suicide.</i>

544
00:38:05,049 --> 00:38:06,584
Well, see you again.

545
00:38:06,651 --> 00:38:08,019
I already told you.

546
00:38:08,085 --> 00:38:09,253
We won't be meeting again.

547
00:38:09,320 --> 00:38:11,088
Is that so?

548
00:38:11,155 --> 00:38:13,924
I am quite certain
you will come to see me, though.

549
00:38:16,394 --> 00:38:17,628
I'll take over.

550
00:38:18,229 --> 00:38:19,263
This way.

551
00:38:48,326 --> 00:38:50,027
You here for a consultation too?

552
00:38:55,733 --> 00:38:57,034
I'm sorry.

553
00:38:58,235 --> 00:38:59,970
That won't be possible today.

554
00:39:05,443 --> 00:39:06,711
Kenshin…

555
00:39:13,217 --> 00:39:14,752
You should stay out of this.

556
00:41:01,225 --> 00:41:03,427
<i>Narita's son has turned himself in.</i>

557
00:41:04,228 --> 00:41:05,896
<i>Is he actually talking this time?</i>

558
00:41:06,664 --> 00:41:08,265
<i>He's incredibly cooperative.</i>

559
00:41:10,768 --> 00:41:12,203
How is Makoto?

560
00:41:12,269 --> 00:41:14,672
He's completely back to his usual self.

561
00:41:15,439 --> 00:41:17,608
Well, that is troublesome too.

562
00:41:20,578 --> 00:41:22,680
You said something before.

563
00:41:22,746 --> 00:41:23,781
What?

564
00:41:24,281 --> 00:41:26,450
That you and Mr. Tagusari go way back.

565
00:41:27,985 --> 00:41:29,653
We're from the same hometown.

566
00:41:31,055 --> 00:41:32,656
Are you connected by those murders?

567
00:41:34,758 --> 00:41:35,759
What?

568
00:41:36,861 --> 00:41:38,829
April 26, 1995.

569
00:41:38,896 --> 00:41:42,666
The Yomogida-cho family murder case.

570
00:41:46,003 --> 00:41:49,006
The culprit still hasn't been caught.

571
00:41:52,209 --> 00:41:53,844
The statute has expired, you know.

572
00:41:59,216 --> 00:42:00,784
What about the evidence?

573
00:42:01,619 --> 00:42:02,653
Did you find it?

574
00:42:05,155 --> 00:42:06,790
I made sure to search thoroughly.

575
00:42:07,291 --> 00:42:10,127
I'll run to the supermarket.
Keep working on that.

576
00:42:24,842 --> 00:42:27,578
But there was nothing there.

577
00:42:33,317 --> 00:42:34,285
Really?

578
00:42:36,353 --> 00:42:37,354
Yes.

579
00:42:38,122 --> 00:42:41,458
So, you don't need to worry all that much.

580
00:42:41,525 --> 00:42:42,927
You really want…

581
00:42:44,795 --> 00:42:47,064
to protect those brothers, huh?

582
00:43:06,183 --> 00:43:07,818
<i>Now we have Tsuda's notebook</i>…

583
00:43:07,885 --> 00:43:11,055
<i>We should be able to find out</i>
<i>what happened 30 years ago.</i>

584
00:43:12,022 --> 00:43:15,526
"However, the darkness surrounding
the illicit manufacturing runs deep.

585
00:43:16,060 --> 00:43:17,194
The involved parties

586
00:43:17,861 --> 00:43:21,131
include the Karashima Metal Factory,
the Igarashi-gumi,

587
00:43:22,066 --> 00:43:23,334
and beyond that…"

588
00:43:25,803 --> 00:43:27,671
Who could it be at a time like this?

589
00:43:36,146 --> 00:43:37,281
Why?

590
00:43:51,729 --> 00:43:52,863
<i>You don't think…</i>

591
00:43:52,930 --> 00:43:54,398
<i>Mr. Koike was involved too?</i>

592
00:43:54,465 --> 00:43:56,600
Everyone will continue to be happy.

593
00:43:56,667 --> 00:43:58,669
Do you trust Tsuda more?!

594
00:43:58,736 --> 00:44:00,971
<i>Do you want to know the truth that badly?</i>

595
00:44:01,739 --> 00:44:02,706
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.
